snippet: Three arms of government in Topeka, Kan., have been at an impasse over who should be responsible for — and pay for — prosecuting people accused of misdemeanor cases of domestic violence.
lead_paragraph: Three arms of government in Topeka, Kan., have been at an impasse over who should be responsible for — and pay for — prosecuting people accused of misdemeanor cases of domestic violence.

headline.main: Facing Cuts, a City Repeals Its Domestic Violence Law
headline.print_headline: Facing Cuts, a City Repeals Its Domestic Violence Law
